---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SEO from '../components/SEO.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service | Everdantia" description="Terms of Service for Everdantia NFT collection and platform usage.">
	<SEO 
		title="Terms of Service | Everdantia"
		description="Terms of Service for Everdantia NFT collection and platform usage."
		canonical="https://everdantia.art/terms"
	/>

	<main class="terms-page">
		<div class="container">
			<header class="page-header">
				<h1>Terms of Service</h1>
				<p class="last-updated">Last updated: August 19, 2025</p>
			</header>

			<div class="content">
				<section>
					<h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
					<p>By accessing and using the Everdantia website and services, you accept and agree to be bound by the terms and provision of this agreement. If you do not agree to abide by the above, please do not use this service.</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>2. NFT Collection Overview</h2>
					<p>Everdantia is a collection of unique digital artworks (NFTs) representing trees in a magical forest. Each NFT is stored on the Ethereum blockchain and represents ownership of a unique digital asset.</p>
					<h3>2.1 What You Own</h3>
					<ul>
						<li>You own the NFT token and the associated digital artwork</li>
						<li>You have the right to display, sell, or transfer your NFT</li>
						<li>You do NOT own the underlying intellectual property or copyright</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>3. Intellectual Property</h2>
					<p>Everdantia retains all intellectual property rights to the artwork, characters, stories, and brand elements. NFT ownership grants you:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Personal, non-commercial use rights</li>
						<li>Right to display your NFT publicly</li>
						<li>Right to include in personal collections or galleries</li>
					</ul>
					<p><strong>Commercial use requires separate licensing agreement.</strong></p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>4. Environmental Impact & Conservation</h2>
					<p>Everdantia is committed to environmental responsibility:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>A portion of proceeds supports real-world reforestation efforts</li>
						<li>We use energy-efficient blockchain solutions where possible</li>
						<li>Conservation partnerships are maintained transparently</li>
					</ul>
					<p>Environmental claims are made in good faith based on available information and partnerships.</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>5. Marketplace & Trading</h2>
					<h3>5.1 Primary Sales</h3>
					<p>NFTs may be purchased directly from Everdantia through authorized channels.</p>
					<h3>5.2 Secondary Sales</h3>
					<p>You may resell your NFTs on compatible marketplaces. Everdantia may receive royalties from secondary sales as programmed into the smart contract.</p>
					<h3>5.3 Pricing</h3>
					<p>All prices are set in cryptocurrency (ETH) and are subject to blockchain transaction fees.</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>6. Prohibited Uses</h2>
					<p>You may not use Everdantia NFTs for:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Commercial purposes without licensing</li>
						<li>Creating derivative works for commercial gain</li>
						<li>Promoting hate speech, violence, or illegal activities</li>
						<li>Trademark or copyright infringement</li>
						<li>Any use that damages the Everdantia brand</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>7. Platform Disclaimer</h2>
					<p>Everdantia platform is provided "as is" without warranties:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>We do not guarantee platform availability</li>
						<li>Blockchain transactions are irreversible</li>
						<li>Technical issues may affect functionality</li>
						<li>Third-party integrations are not under our control</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
					<p>Everdantia's liability is limited to the maximum extent permitted by law. We are not liable for:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Loss of cryptocurrency or NFTs due to user error</li>
						<li>Blockchain network issues or fees</li>
						<li>Third-party marketplace problems</li>
						<li>Changes in NFT value or market conditions</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>9. Privacy & Data</h2>
					<p>Your privacy is important. Please review our <a href="/privacy" class="link">Privacy Policy</a> for details on data collection and use.</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>10. Modifications</h2>
					<p>We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Significant changes will be announced via:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Website notification</li>
						<li>Email to registered users</li>
						<li>Community Discord announcements</li>
					</ul>
					<p>Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance.</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>11. Termination</h2>
					<p>We may terminate or suspend access for violations of these terms. NFT ownership rights remain unaffected by platform access termination.</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>12. Governing Law</h2>
					<p>These terms are governed by the laws of [Your Jurisdiction]. Disputes will be resolved through binding arbitration where legally permitted.</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2>13. Contact Information</h2>
					<p>For questions about these Terms of Service:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Email: <a href="mailto:legal@everdantia.art" class="link">legal@everdantia.art</a></li>
						<li>Discord: <a href="https://discord.gg/gJzaprRj" target="_blank" class="link">Everdantia Community</a></li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<div class="effective-notice">
					<p><strong>Note:</strong> This Terms of Service is effective as of the last updated date above. Previous versions are available upon request.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	.terms-page {
		min-height: 100vh;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f4a3c 0%, #1a5f4f 50%, #0f4a3c 100%);
		color: #ffffff;
		padding: 2rem 0;
	}

	.container {
		max-width: 900px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 0 1.5rem;
	}

	.page-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
		padding: 2rem 0;
		border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
	}

	.page-header h1 {
		font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
		font-weight: 700;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ffffff, #a8d5ba);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		line-height: 1.2;
	}

	.last-updated {
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		opacity: 0.8;
		font-style: italic;
	}

	.content {
		line-height: 1.7;
		max-width: none; /* Override any prose max-width */
	}

	section {
		margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
		padding: 2rem;
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
		border-radius: 12px;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
	}

	h2 {
		color: #a8d5ba;
		font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 1.5rem);
		font-weight: 600;
		margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(168, 213, 186, 0.3);
		padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
		line-height: 1.3;
	}

	h3 {
		color: #c2e0d0;
		font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2.5vw, 1.2rem);
		font-weight: 500;
		margin: 1.5rem 0 0.75rem 0;
		line-height: 1.3;
	}

	p {
		margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
		font-size: 1rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		max-width: 75ch; /* Optimal reading width */
	}

	ul {
		margin: 1.25rem 0;
		padding-left: 1.5rem;
	}

	li {
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
		line-height: 1.6;
		font-size: 1rem;
	}

	.link {
		color: #a8d5ba;
		text-decoration: none;
		border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
		transition: all 0.3s ease;
	}

	.link:hover {
		color: #ffffff;
		border-bottom-color: #a8d5ba;
	}

	.effective-notice {
		margin-top: 3rem;
		padding: 1.5rem;
		background: rgba(168, 213, 186, 0.1);
		border-radius: 8px;
		border-left: 4px solid #a8d5ba;
	}

	.effective-notice p {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
	}

	strong {
		color: #ffffff;
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.container {
			padding: 0 1rem;
		}

		.page-header h1 {
			font-size: 2rem;
		}

		section {
			padding: 1rem;
		}

		h2 {
			font-size: 1.3rem;
		}
	}
</style>
